{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"51f02f4f-5628-42a1-8bd7-4bfc9ebb6c6f","content":"There are no workflow files in the current directory, so I can't review your specific workflow. Here's a general guide for switching from `secrets.NUGET_API_KEY` to **NuGet trusted publishing (OIDC)**:\n\n---\n\n### 1. NuGet.org setup\n- Go to **nuget.org → Manage Packages → your package → Trusted Publishers**\n- Add a new GitHub Actions publisher, specifying your **repo owner**, **repo name**, **workflow file name**, and optionally an **environment name**\n\n### 2. Workflow changes\n\n**Add `id-token: write` permission** (required for OIDC):\n\n```yaml\npermissions:\n  id-token: write   # request OIDC token\n  contents: read\n```\n\n**Replace the `dotnet nuget push` step:**\n\n```yaml\n# OLD — remove this:\n- run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg --api-key ${{ secrets.NUGET_API_KEY }} --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n\n# NEW — use trusted publishing:\n- run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n  env:\n    NUGET_AUTH_TOKEN: \"\"   # not needed; OIDC handles auth\n```\n\nActually, the simplest approach is to use the **`dotnet nuget push` with `--api-key`** replaced by the OIDC flow. As of the latest NuGet support:\n\n```yaml\n- name: Push to NuGet (OIDC)\n  run: |\n    dotnet nuget add source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json \\\n      --name nuget.org \\\n      --store-password-in-clear-text \\\n      --username \"az\" \\\n      --password ${{ steps.oidc.outputs.id-token }}\n    dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg --source nuget.org\n```\n\nOr, more typically, use the **`nuget/setup-nuget`** action with trusted publishing:\n\n```yaml\njobs:\n  publish:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    permissions:\n      id-token: write\n      contents: read\n    environment: nuget-publish  # optional but recommended\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n      - uses: actions/setup-dotnet@v4\n      - run: dotnet pack -c Release\n\n      - name: Publish to NuGet (trusted publishing)\n        uses: nuget/publish@v1\n        with:\n          package-files: '**/*.nupkg'\n          nuget-server: https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\n### 3. Clean up\n- Remove `NUGET_API_KEY` from your repository secrets once verified\n- Delete/revoke the API key on nuget.org\n\n### Key benefits\n- **No secrets to rotate** — authentication uses short-lived OIDC tokens\n- **Scoped** — only your specific workflow/repo/environment can publish\n\nWould you like me to create or update a specific workflow file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"114ced58-ef6d-4b06-b72f-07532b28d633","outputTokens":746,"requestId":"B455:32BB22:71A2B15:7D1E02D:69F156DF"},"id":"27b2a5a2-bca8-43ec-9a74-cf2e2cb57c27","timestamp":"2026-04-29T00:55:10.518Z","parentId":"d66c82d9-e8a3-4b59-919a-b987bb1c61fe"}
